  - Data Language Models tabular foundation model (arXiv 2605.06290) — generic ML
  - AI CFD Scientist (arXiv 2605.06607) — not biomedical
  - Automated Clinical Report Generation for cognitive remediation (arXiv 2605.06594) — narrower clinical
  - Navigating by Old Maps — LLM mech interp post-training (arXiv 2605.06076) — not biomedical

### Why GATHER won

Directly in Su Lab's KG/RAG wheelhouse and complements rather than overlaps the day's three prior episodes (clinical agent, generative protein design, agent benchmarking). The convergence-node retrieval primitive — global topology-aware traversal replacing entity-wise expansion + iterative LLM reasoning — is portable to any biology problem with many noisy entities pointing at one latent answer (pathway analysis, multi-symptom diagnosis, GWAS hit interpretation, polypharmacology), so the architectural lesson lands beyond cell typing. The morning's funnel had explicitly flagged GATHER as a strong candidate ("interesting, candidate for next week") deferred only to avoid stacking; the deferral cleared once the day's other slots were committed.

